% body -------------------------

% question 1
\begin{q}[12 points]

  A roulette wheel has 38 slots, numbered 0,00, and then 1
  through 36. The slots 0 and 00 are colored green, 18 of
  the other slots are red and 18 are black. The dealer spins
  the wheel and, at the same time, rolls a small ball along
  along the wheel in the opposite direction. The wheel is
  carefully balanced so that the ball is equally likely to
  land in any slot when the wheel slows. gambles can bet on
  various combinations of numbers and colors.
  \begin{enumerate}
  \item What is the probability that the ball will land in
    any one slot?
  \item If you bet on ``red'' you win if the ball lands in a
    red slot. What is the probability of winning with this
    bet?
  \item The slot numbers a laid out on a board on which
    gamblers place their bets. One column of numbers on the
    board contains all multiples of 3, that is
    3,6,9,...,36. You place a ``column bet'' that wins if
    any of these numbers comes up. What is your probability
    of winning?
  \end{enumerate}
  
\end{q}


